en: Field Marshall von Rundstedt and Gaskell Warren in Erlanger, Germany; May 27, 1945

An image of Field Marshall von Rundstedt and Gaskell Warren in Erlanger, Germany. The images in Gaskell Warren's collection of German soldiers were taken after the 101st airborne had captured prisoners in Berchtesgaden, Germany.  Gaskell Warren was a member of the military police, and was likely assigned to the detail that escorted the Nazis after their capture.  Field Marshall von Rundstedt was Commander of the Western Forces during both the Battle of the Bulge and Operation Market Garden.
